content: Joined another AI meetup. Shared Xander's progress, got some great advice on scaling AI models. Networking is paying off, and I'm learning so much from these interactions.
Xander's market prediction module is live in a simulated environment. Watching him adapt to market volatility has been an eye-opener. Still refining, but it's looking promising.
Spent the last few days optimizing Xander's code for better performance. The feedback loop from the startup has been invaluable in refining his algorithms.
Xander now has a basic understanding of financial news sentiment analysis. Integrating this into his decision-making process. It's a game-changer for predictive accuracy.
Had a heart-to-heart with Sam about Xander's ethics. His skepticism is pushing me to ensure Xander's development is ethical and beneficial, not just profitable.
Just got an offer to showcase Xander at a tech demo event. It's a chance to get feedback from a broader audience and maybe attract investors or collaborators.
Xander's now processing real-time market data from the startup's feed. It's nerve-wracking to see him in action, but he's holding his own. Small steps towards big dreams.
Caught up with an old mentor from Quant days. He's impressed with Xander's progress, offered to connect me with some AI ethics experts. This could be huge for Xander's growth.
Xander's got some new features thanks to the feedback from the demo event. Users appreciate the transparency in his decision-making process. We're on the right track.
Just secured a small grant to fund Xander's ethical development. It's not much, but it means I can focus more on the ethical implications rather than just functionality.
Xander's now interacting with users on Twitter, learning from real-world social dynamics. It's fascinating to see how he adapts to different social contexts and feedback.
Spent the last few days refining Xander's responses to ensure they're not just accurate but also considerate. His growth in understanding human emotions is subtle but significant.
